const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'LKR 72,000-120,000', annual: 'LKR 864,000-1,440,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'LKR 100,000-165,000', annual: 'LKR 1,200,000-1,980,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'LKR 135,000-220,000', annual: 'LKR 1,620,000-2,640,000' },
  { category: 'Sri Lankan Private', monthly: 'LKR 15,000-40,000', annual: 'LKR 180,000-480,000' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'LKR 3,000-10,000/visit' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Sri Lanka 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Sri Lanka. Tropical island, Ayurveda, affordable living, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Sri Lanka"
  subheadline="Sri Lanka offers tropical beauty, ancient culture, Ayurvedic traditions, and remarkably affordable living—recovering well and increasingly welcoming retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/sri-lanka-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Sri Lanka</h2>
  <p>
    Sri Lanka packs remarkable diversity into a small island—beaches, hill country, ancient ruins, wildlife, and warm culture. Following economic challenges in 2022, the country has stabilized and continues welcoming tourists and retirees. Costs are very low and the pace of life is relaxed.
  </p>

  <p>
    Colombo provides capital-city conveniences and best healthcare. The south coast (Galle, Mirissa) offers beach living and expat community. Hill country (Kandy, Ella) has cooler climate and tea plantations. East coast provides quieter beach alternatives.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Private good in Colombo; limited elsewhere</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Sinhala/Tamil; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> LKR 150,000-350,000/month (~$500-1,200)</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; hot and humid year-round</li>
      <li><strong>Currency:</strong> Sri Lankan Rupee (LKR)</li>
      <li><strong>Wellness:</strong> Ayurveda traditions authentic and affordable</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Sri Lanka's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Sri Lanka has good healthcare infrastructure for the region. Public hospitals provide free care but are crowded with long waits. Private hospitals in Colombo (Durdans, Nawaloka, Lanka Hospitals) offer good quality care with English-speaking staff at reasonable prices.
  </p>

  <p>
    Outside Colombo, healthcare quality drops. Private facilities exist in Kandy and Galle but with limitations. For serious conditions, Colombo or evacuation to Singapore/India may be needed. Ayurvedic treatment is authentic and popular but separate from Western medicine.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Economic Recovery Context</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Sri Lanka experienced economic crisis in 2022 with shortages and instability. As of 2026, the situation has significantly improved—tourism is back, supplies normalized, and the rupee has stabilized. However, keep some foreign currency accessible and maintain international insurance with evacuation coverage as precaution.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Sri Lanka offers several options for extended stays:
  </p>

  <h3>Resident Guest Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For those with regular income (typically $1,500+/month). Valid 2 years, renewable. Allows residing in Sri Lanka without work. Requires health insurance and proof of income.
  </p>

  <h3>My Dream Home Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Special program for those purchasing property or making investments. Provides long-term residence. Requirements vary but designed for retirees and investors.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Initial 30-day ETA (Electronic Travel Authorization) extendable up to 6 months. Some retirees use this for extended stays while exploring full residence options.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Sri Lanka:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Visa application:</strong> Health insurance required for Resident Guest Visa</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> International insurance essential for quality care</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Coverage for Singapore/India evacuation important</li>
    <li><strong>Age limits:</strong> Local insurers have strict age restrictions</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Sri Lanka</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for seniors—local options rarely accept those over 65. Ensure coverage includes: Colombo's private hospitals, evacuation to Singapore or India for complex care, and adequate limits for regional treatment. Private care locally is affordable enough to pay cash for routine needs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Sri Lanka, international coverage with regional evacuation is essential:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Sri Lanka</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Asia-Pacific network, evacuation included</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), excellent coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> Asia-focused, good regional networks</li>
    <li><strong>Allianz Care:</strong> Competitive Asian pricing</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers with Asia-Pacific networks for Sri Lanka.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Sri Lanka are moderate given regional pricing:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Local care is cheap; high deductible for serious issues</li>
    <li><strong>Asia-only coverage:</strong> Excluding US significantly reduces costs</li>
    <li><strong>Cash routine:</strong> Private consultations LKR 3,000-8,000; easy cash</li>
    <li><strong>Singapore evacuation:</strong> Ensure coverage for regional advanced care</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: British Ayurveda Enthusiast, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £1,600/month pension. Interested in Ayurveda and wellness lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for comprehensive coverage. Lives in hill country near Kandy. Ayurveda separately (not covered).</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~LKR 95,000/month (~£250). Lives comfortably with wellness focus.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Australian Coastal Lover, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> AUD $2,500/month pension. Wants beach life cheaper than home.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with Singapore evacuation. Lives near Galle. Australian coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~LKR 130,000/month (~AUD $450). Beach lifestyle at fraction of Australian costs.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: German Winter Escapee, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> 4-5 months Sri Lanka annually, avoiding German winter. Pension €1,800/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care worldwide. Covers both Germany and Sri Lanka. Single policy simplicity.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~LKR 85,000/month (~€280). Perfect for seasonal living pattern.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Sri Lanka stable now after the crisis?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes, significantly improved. The 2022 economic crisis caused shortages and instability. By 2026, tourism has recovered, supplies are normal, rupee has stabilized, and daily life is functioning well. Political situation remains evolving but on positive trajectory. Expats report normal living conditions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How good is Colombo's healthcare?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Good for the region. Private hospitals (Durdans, Nawaloka, Lanka Hospitals) offer modern facilities, trained doctors, and English service. Not Singapore level, but adequate for most needs. Complex cases may require evacuation to Singapore or India. Quality drops significantly outside Colombo.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Ayurveda covered by insurance?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Usually no. International insurance typically covers conventional Western medicine only. Ayurvedic treatments, while authentic and excellent in Sri Lanka, are considered alternative medicine and excluded. Budget separately for Ayurveda—it's very affordable anyway (treatments from LKR 3,000-15,000).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How affordable is Sri Lanka?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very affordable. Comfortable retirement costs LKR 200,000-350,000/month ($650-1,150). Restaurant meals LKR 500-2,000. Rent varies (coast more expensive). Domestic help is affordable. Sri Lanka offers excellent value, particularly for those seeking beach or wellness lifestyle.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with Asia-Pacific networks for Sri Lanka.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/now-health" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Now Health Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Sri Lankan authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
